t of neutrino-nucleus interactions also\nallows us to exclude any further effects of the $\\nu$ process on stable nuclei\nand to quantify the effects on numerous, hitherto unconsidered radioactive\nnuclei, e.g., $^{36}$Cl, $^{72}$As, $^{84}$Rb, and $^{88}$Y.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 May 2018 16:15:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
